T1  - Arbitrage pricing, transaction costs and taxation of capital gains: A study of government bonds with the same maturity date
AU  - Litzenberger, Robert H.
AU  - Rolfo, Jacques
JO  - Journal of Financial Economics
VL  - 13
IS  - 3
SP  - 337
EP  - 351
PY  - 1984
DA  - 1984/09/01/
SN  - 0304-405X
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-405X(84)90003-5
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304405X84900035
AB  - This paper examines one of the few cases of seemingly redundant securities: sets of three government bonds with the same maturity date. Within the bounds on relative bond prices established by tax-exempt investors in a market with proportional transaction costs, the taxation of capital gains on the basis of realization has a significant impact on relative prices. The empirical evidence supports the tax option effect discussed by Constantinides and Ingersoll, but does not generally support the segmented tax-clientele equilibrium discussed by Schaefer.
